♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

04:36.319 --> 04:37.886
-MANNY: SO YOU LIKE MY
JOKE? [CHUCKLING]

04:38.016 --> 04:39.061
HEY, WHAT'S UP, NEWMIE?

04:39.191 --> 04:40.845
IT'S A KITE FLYING CONTEST.

04:40.976 --> 04:42.847
-KITE FLYING?

04:42.978 --> 04:43.935
-NEWMIE: YEAH.
BAYWATCH IS
HELPING RAISE FUNDS

04:44.066 --> 04:45.372
FOR THE JUVENILE
DIABETES FOUNDATION.

04:45.502 --> 04:46.851
"THE ONLY REMEDY IS
A CURE" CAMPAIGN.

04:46.982 --> 04:48.418
--JUVENILE DIABETES.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.507
YEAH, MY UNCLE,
CAESAR, HAS DIABETES.

04:50.638 --> 04:52.727
A KID GETTING
IT REALLY SUCKS.

04:52.857 --> 04:54.294
-YEAH, BUT THE
KEY IS TO BELIEVE

04:54.424 --> 04:56.296
THAT HAVING DIABETES
WON'T PREVENT YOU

04:56.426 --> 04:57.819
FROM LIVING A FULL
AND ACTIVE LIFE.

04:57.949 --> 04:59.690
-WELL, I HAD A FRIEND
BACK IN GREEN BAY

04:59.821 --> 05:02.127
THAT'S A DIABETIC AND SHE
WAS ON THE GYMNASTICS TEAM.

05:02.258 --> 05:03.912
SHE HAD TO
HAVE INSULIN SHOTS

05:04.042 --> 05:05.740
EVERY DAY JUST TO KEEP HER
BLOOD SUGAR LEVELS NORMAL.

05:06.349 --> 05:07.481
WHEN YOU GOTTA
BALANCE THE FOOD

05:07.611 --> 05:08.830
WITH THE EXERCISE
AND THE INSULIN,

05:08.960 --> 05:10.310
FOOD MAKES THE LEVELS GO UP,

05:10.440 --> 05:11.963
EXERCISE AND INSULIN
MAKES IT GO DOWN.

05:12.094 --> 05:13.748
-MM-HMM.
-WELL, WHAT DO
YOU SAY, YOU GUYS?

05:13.878 --> 05:15.315
THERE'S A TROPHY IN IT.
YOU IN?

05:15.445 --> 05:16.751
-AH, I DON'T KNOW.

05:16.881 --> 05:18.274
-YOU KNOW, I'VE
NEVER BUILT ONE.

05:18.405 --> 05:19.536
SOUNDS LIKE FUN,

05:19.667 --> 05:21.625
AND I COULD USE THE TROPHY.

05:21.756 --> 05:23.148
COUNT ME IN. [GIGGLING]
-I NEVER BUILT ONE, EITHER,

05:23.279 --> 05:24.585
BUT I KNOW I CAN
BUILD A BETTER ONE

05:24.715 --> 05:26.674
THAN SOME CHEESE-HEAD
FROM WISCONSIN.

05:26.804 --> 05:27.762
COUNT ME IN.

05:28.763 --> 05:29.590
-THAT'S IT.

05:31.418 --> 05:33.768
CHEESE HEAD.

05:33.898 --> 05:38.903
-[OMINOUS MUSIC]

06:41.662 --> 06:42.663
-[COUGHING]

06:50.061 --> 06:51.062
-[GLASS SMASHING]

07:04.467 --> 07:05.860
-THIS IS SCARAB ONE,

07:05.990 --> 07:06.904
I GOT A BOAT FIRE
RIGHT OFF POINT DUNE.

07:07.035 --> 07:07.862
MAN: UH, ROGER SCARAB ONE,

07:07.992 --> 07:08.950
WE COPY YOUR RESCUE.

07:09.080 --> 07:14.129
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

07:32.495 --> 07:34.062
-MITCH: COME ON, COME ON,

07:34.192 --> 07:34.845
WE'RE GETTING OUTTA
HERE, COME ON!
I GOTCHA.

07:34.976 --> 07:35.890
-[COUGHING]

07:39.981 --> 07:41.243
READY? JUMP!

08:11.186 --> 08:11.969
FEELING BETTER?

08:12.100 --> 08:13.405
-YES, THANK YOU.

08:13.536 --> 08:14.406
-GOOD.

08:14.537 --> 08:15.756
-YOU SAVED MY LIFE.

08:16.278 --> 08:17.322
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOUR NAME.

08:17.453 --> 08:19.237
-IT'S MITCH, MITCH BUCHANNON.

08:19.368 --> 08:20.674
-OH, WELL, THANK YOU.

08:20.804 --> 08:21.979
THANK YOU, MITCH BUCHANNON.

08:25.722 --> 08:28.246
-SO UH, SARA, I DON'T
KNOW YOUR LAST NAME.

08:28.377 --> 08:30.466
-CHAPMAN.
-SARA CHAPMAN.

08:30.597 --> 08:31.728
ADDRESS?

08:32.424 --> 08:34.601
-UM, WELL ACTUALLY,
I DON'T HAVE ONE YET.

08:34.731 --> 08:35.732
I'M FROM OUT OF TOWN.

08:35.863 --> 08:38.518
I'M FROM TEXAS,
EL PASO, TEXAS.

08:39.606 --> 08:41.042
I'D NEVER SEEN
THE PACIFIC OCEAN,

08:41.172 --> 08:43.392
SO I JUST, I RENTED
A BOAT AND...

08:43.957 --> 08:45.089
[SIGHING]

08:46.351 --> 08:47.439
-WHAT HAPPENED OUT THERE?

08:48.310 --> 08:49.877
-IT WAS A REALLY
STUPID THING.

08:50.007 --> 08:51.661
AND IT WAS MY FAULT, I JUST,

08:52.314 --> 08:54.577
TRIPPED OVER A CAN
OF GASOLINE, AND,

08:54.708 --> 08:56.318
WELL, I WAS
SMOKING A CIGARETTE.

08:56.448 --> 08:57.711
IT'S A REALLY
DUMB, DUMB THING.

08:58.320 --> 08:59.147
-YOU WERE PRETTY LUCKY.

08:59.277 --> 09:00.583
-SARA: YEAH, I KNOW.

09:00.714 --> 09:02.542
YOU KNOW, IF YOU
HADN'T COME ALONG, I'D,

09:02.672 --> 09:04.065
I'D BE DEAD FOR SURE.

09:06.328 --> 09:08.678
-[PHONE RINGING]
-UM, EXCUSE ME.

09:10.375 --> 09:12.290
BUCHANNON.
HEY, DARLIN'!

09:12.421 --> 09:14.031
YEAH, I'LL PICK UP
THE DRY CLEANING.

09:14.162 --> 09:15.642
DOES THE BABY
NEED ANYTHING?

09:16.251 --> 09:17.818
OK.
SEE YA.

09:19.167 --> 09:20.255
-YOUR WIFE?

09:20.385 --> 09:21.996
NO, THAT'S MY MOM.
-HMM.

09:22.126 --> 09:23.563
AND THE BABY?

09:23.693 --> 09:25.477
UH, A FRIEND OF MINE
NAMED NEELY'S DAUGHTER.

09:25.608 --> 09:26.827
SHE'S STAYING WITH
ME FOR A WHILE,

09:26.957 --> 09:29.133
AND SHE'S IN SAN
DIEGO ON BUSINESS

09:29.264 --> 09:30.308
SO MY MOM'S BABYSITTING.

09:30.439 --> 09:31.614
IT'S A LONG STORY.

09:31.745 --> 09:33.050
UM, BE BACK IN A
COUPLE OF MINUTES,

09:33.181 --> 09:34.051
FINISH YOUR TEA, HUH?

09:34.182 --> 09:35.052
-THANK YOU.

09:36.924 --> 09:41.363
-[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC]

10:01.862 --> 10:03.298
-NEWMIE: ALL RIGHT.

10:03.428 --> 10:04.560
YOU GUYS ARE GONNA LOVE
FISHING ON THIS PIER.

10:04.691 --> 10:05.953
WHEN I WAS A KID,

10:06.083 --> 10:08.695
I USED TO CATCH
BLUEFIN TUNA THIS BIG

10:08.825 --> 10:09.826
OFF THE END OF THIS THING.

10:09.957 --> 10:11.523
IT WAS UNBELIEVABLE .

10:11.654 --> 10:12.873
IT'S ONE OF THE BEST
FISHING SPOTS ON THE COAST.

10:13.482 --> 10:14.657
HEY, THERE'S SOME ICE CREAM.

10:14.788 --> 10:15.832
COME ON, I'LL BUY.

10:15.963 --> 10:17.181
ANYTHING YOU GUYS WANT.

10:19.140 --> 10:19.967
-HEY!

10:20.097 --> 10:21.185
NEWMIE, WHAT'S GOING ON?

10:21.316 --> 10:22.883
-WELL, I'M JUST
TAKING MY NEPHEW

10:23.013 --> 10:25.015
AND A FEW OF HIS
BUDDIES FISHING.
-OH, THAT'S SO NICE.

10:25.146 --> 10:26.495
I REMEMBER MY UNCLE FRANK

10:26.626 --> 10:27.714
USED TO TAKE ME AND
MY BROTHER FISHING

10:27.844 --> 10:29.411
EVERY SATURDAY MORNING.

10:29.541 --> 10:30.891
WE'D GET UP EARLY AND HAVE
BREAKFAST ON THE LAKE.

10:31.021 --> 10:32.675
CREAM CHEESE AND
PICKLED HERRING.

10:32.806 --> 10:35.504
-CREAM CHEESE AND PICKLED
HERRING FOR BREAKFAST?

10:35.635 --> 10:36.940
NO WONDER YOU
LEFT WISCONSIN.

10:37.071 --> 10:38.550
-HEY.

10:38.681 --> 10:39.508
DON'T KNOCK IT UNLESS
YOU'VE TRIED IT.

10:39.639 --> 10:42.032
-NEWMIE: [LAUGHING]
NO THANKS!

10:42.598 --> 10:43.468
WHAT'S WRONG?

10:44.339 --> 10:45.688
-I CAN'T EAT THAT STUFF.

10:45.819 --> 10:47.255
-DIDN'T THEY HAVE
ANY WITHOUT SUGAR?

10:47.385 --> 10:48.430
TODD: WOULDN'T MAKE
A DIFFERENCE, ANYWAY.

10:48.560 --> 10:49.779
-NEWMIE: SORRY.

10:49.910 --> 10:50.998
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

10:51.128 --> 10:52.390
I DON'T EVEN LIKE ICE CREAM.

10:52.521 --> 10:54.915
-WELL, WHAT ABOUT SOME
POPCORN OR A SOFT PRETZEL?

10:56.046 --> 10:57.569
I'M NOT HUNGRY.

10:57.700 --> 10:58.309
COME ON, YOU WERE
STARVING IN THE CAR

10:58.440 --> 10:58.919
ON THE WAY DOWN HERE.

10:59.049 --> 10:59.963
-I LIED, OK?

11:02.531 --> 11:04.446
-LISTEN. I'D LIKE TO
MEET SOMEONE I WORK WITH.

11:04.576 --> 11:05.795
APRIL GIMINSKI.
SHE'S FROM GREEN BAY.

11:05.926 --> 11:07.318
YOU'RE A BIG PACKER
FAN, AREN'T YA?

11:07.449 --> 11:09.016
-NO. I HATE FOOTBALL.

11:11.409 --> 11:12.889
-IT'S NICE TO
MEET YOU, TODD.

11:13.020 --> 11:14.891
-WHATEVER.

11:15.022 --> 11:17.285
I'M GONNA GO PLAY
SOME VIDEO GAMES.
GOT ANY QUARTERS?

11:17.415 --> 11:18.721
-WHAT HAPPENED TO FISHING?

11:18.852 --> 11:19.853
-JUST COME GET ME
WHEN THEY'RE DONE.

11:22.682 --> 11:24.379
-GUYS, WE'RE GONNA
FISH RIGHT HERE.

11:24.509 --> 11:26.337
THIS IS A GREAT PLACE,
RIGHT ON THIS RAIL HERE.

11:26.468 --> 11:27.338
BOY: OK!

11:29.558 --> 11:30.472
-[NEWMIE SIGHS]

11:30.602 --> 11:31.865
HE'S NOT IN THE BEST MOOD.

11:36.913 --> 11:38.262
-SO HOW COME HE
COULDN'T HAVE ICE CREAM?

11:38.393 --> 11:39.350
IS HE ON A SPECIAL DIET?

11:39.960 --> 11:40.830
-HE'S DIABETIC.

11:41.831 --> 11:42.789
-OH.

11:42.919 --> 11:44.138
SO THAT'S WHY YOU'RE SO INTO

11:44.268 --> 11:45.748
THE JUVENILE
DIABETES FOUNDATION.

11:46.662 --> 11:47.924
-YEAH, IT HITS
PRETTY CLOSE TO HOME.

11:48.055 --> 11:49.926
TODD FOUND OUT HE
HAD IT A YEAR AGO.

11:50.057 --> 11:51.319
IT'S BEEN HARD ON HIM.

11:51.449 --> 11:52.929
-I CAN IMAGINE.

11:53.060 --> 11:54.844
BUT IT DOESN'T MEAN THAT
IT HAS TO PREVENT HIM

11:54.975 --> 11:56.237
FROM LEADING A NORMAL LIFE.

11:56.367 --> 11:57.978
I WISH YOU COULD
CONVINCE HIM OF THAT.

12:01.242 --> 12:02.373
-APRIL: LOOK AT THOSE GUYS!

12:03.635 --> 12:04.811
-SINCE WHEN DID THEY START

12:04.941 --> 12:06.160
LETTING STREET
PERFORMERS ON THE PIER?

12:06.769 --> 12:08.162
-WELL, MAYBE THEY
HAVE A PERMIT.

12:08.292 --> 12:10.338
-[AUDIENCE APPLAUDING]

12:10.468 --> 12:11.513
-MAN: WATCH ME NOW!

12:13.950 --> 12:15.386
-WELL THEY DON'T HAVE
A PERMIT FOR THAT.

12:15.517 --> 12:17.171
HEY! GET DOWN!

12:18.955 --> 12:21.392
-WOMAN: HE'S BEEN
PRACTICING THIS FOR A WHILE!

12:31.402 --> 12:32.186
-AH! WHOA!

12:32.316 --> 12:34.971
[SHOUTING]

12:36.190 --> 12:37.713
HELP!

12:41.804 --> 12:42.892
-CALL FOR BACKUP, I'LL
MEET YOU ON THE BEACH!

12:43.023 --> 12:43.893
-RIGHT!

12:44.415 --> 12:48.115
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

13:03.826 --> 13:04.784
-[GRUNTING]

13:14.010 --> 13:15.011
-[SIRENS BLARING]

13:19.842 --> 13:21.322
-NEWMIE: RELAX,
I'VE GOT YOU.

13:21.452 --> 13:23.367
-[SIRENS BLARING]

13:23.498 --> 13:24.368
-[PERFORMER GROANS]

13:24.499 --> 13:26.109
[COUGHING]

13:56.009 --> 13:57.227
-CALL CAR'S ON THE WAY.

13:57.358 --> 13:58.663
-ALL RIGHT.
STABILIZE HIS HEAD.

13:58.794 --> 13:59.664
-OK.

14:02.798 --> 14:04.191
-HEY, LISTEN.

14:04.321 --> 14:06.019
DON'T MOVE ANYTHING,
ESPECIALLY YOUR MOUTH.

14:06.149 --> 14:07.498
-I'M OK.

14:07.629 --> 14:08.325
I JUST GOT THE WIND
KNOCKED OUT OF ME.

14:08.456 --> 14:09.674
LET ME GO, MAN.

14:09.805 --> 14:11.241
-HEY, DID YOU HEAR
WHAT I SAID?

14:11.372 --> 14:12.895
-HEY, WHO IS THIS GUY?

14:13.026 --> 14:14.592
-FORTUNATELY FOR YOU,
HE'S AN OFF-DUTY LIFEGUARD.

14:15.550 --> 14:16.594
-WHICH GOES TO SHOW YOU,

14:16.725 --> 14:18.292
YOU'RE NEVER REALLY OFF-DUTY.

14:30.695 --> 14:31.696
-OH, HI MITCH!

14:32.915 --> 14:33.785
-SARA!

14:34.612 --> 14:35.483
HI.

14:36.440 --> 14:38.747
-AND TALKING ABOUT
GETTING A BREAK,

14:38.878 --> 14:41.054
ASHLEY WAS RUNNING
ME RAGGED TODAY

14:41.184 --> 14:42.533
AND DING DONG THE
DOORBELL RINGS,

14:42.664 --> 14:44.144
AND MY PRAYERS ARE ANSWERED!

14:44.274 --> 14:46.146
AND SHE BRINGS FLOWERS!

14:46.276 --> 14:48.017
-OH, I JUST WANTED
TO SAY THANK YOU AGAIN

14:48.148 --> 14:49.018
FOR SAVING MY LIFE.

14:49.584 --> 14:50.802
YOU DO LIKE FLOWERS,
DON'T YOU?

14:50.933 --> 14:52.804
-MITCH: I, I
MISSED A TURN HERE.

14:53.370 --> 14:54.937
-SARA IS A NANNY, DEAR.

14:55.068 --> 14:56.460
A PROFESSIONAL.

14:56.591 --> 14:58.419
AND SHE HASN'T FOUND
A PLACE TO STAY YET,

14:58.549 --> 15:00.595
SO I THOUGHT MAYBE
SHE COULD HELP US OUT

15:00.725 --> 15:02.379
'TIL NEELY COMES BACK.

15:02.510 --> 15:05.295
AND I CALLED NEELY AND SHE
SAID IT WAS FINE WITH HER.

15:06.035 --> 15:07.428
-UH, WOW!

15:07.558 --> 15:08.472
IT'S, UH, QUITE A DAY.

15:08.603 --> 15:09.386
YOU KNOW, I NEED A BEER.

15:09.517 --> 15:10.300
ANYBODY NEED A BEER?

15:10.431 --> 15:11.432
-SARA: OH, NO THANK YOU.

15:11.562 --> 15:12.955
-WE HARDLY KNOW THIS GIRL!

15:13.086 --> 15:14.391
-BUT SHE SEEMS SO SWEET,

15:14.522 --> 15:16.828
AND SHE HAS LOTS OF
REFERENCES FROM TEXAS.

15:16.959 --> 15:18.134
I'LL CHECK HER OUT.

15:18.265 --> 15:19.788
-NO, LET'S WAIT
AND CHECK HER OUT.

15:19.919 --> 15:21.398
-EXCUSE ME, IF IT
DOESN'T WORK OUT

15:21.529 --> 15:22.922
FOR THE BOTH OF YOU,

15:23.052 --> 15:24.575
THAT'S ALL RIGHT BECAUSE
I DO HAVE ANOTHER OFFER.

15:25.228 --> 15:27.317
-I DON'T WANT TO
LOSE HER, MITCH.

15:27.448 --> 15:28.884
THE BABY LOVES HER,

15:29.015 --> 15:30.407
AND I REALLY NEED IT,
SO THE ANSWER'S YES.

15:30.538 --> 15:32.496
SURE IT IS, DARLING,
YOU KNOW IT IS,

15:32.627 --> 15:33.976
OF COURSE YOU'D SAY YES.

15:34.107 --> 15:35.891
-SARA: SHE IS BEING SO GOOD.

15:36.022 --> 15:36.848
-OH, LET ME TAKE HER.

15:36.979 --> 15:37.806
-SARA: YOU GOT IT.

15:37.937 --> 15:38.938
-YOU'RE WONDERFUL.

15:39.068 --> 15:40.461
SARA: THANK YOU.

15:40.591 --> 15:42.637
UH, MITCH, WHY DON'T
YOU TWO TALK IT OVER

15:42.767 --> 15:44.030
AND SEE WHAT
YOU COME UP WITH?

15:45.379 --> 15:46.597
-YOUR MOM IS SO SWEET.

15:46.728 --> 15:48.469
-YEAH, I KNOW, I KNOW.

15:48.599 --> 15:50.601
-ASHLEY AND NEELY'S KIND OF
LIKE AN INSTANT FAMILY, HUH?

15:50.732 --> 15:52.908
-YEAH, IT'S, IT'S
TEMPORARY, BUT IT'S UH,

15:53.039 --> 15:54.127
IT'S REALLY NICE.

15:54.779 --> 15:55.955
AND NO SMOKING IN THE HOUSE.

15:56.085 --> 15:57.173
-I QUIT TODAY.

15:57.304 --> 15:58.522
I MEAN ALMOST
GETTING BLOWN UP

15:58.653 --> 15:59.567
IS QUITE AN
INCENTIVE. [LAUGHS]

16:04.050 --> 16:06.704
-WELL, WHY DON'T WE JUST TRY
THIS OUT FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

16:07.792 --> 16:08.793
WHEN CAN YOU MOVE IN?

16:08.924 --> 16:10.273
-NOW!

16:10.404 --> 16:11.709
I JUST BROUGHT A FEW
THINGS FROM TEXAS,

16:11.840 --> 16:13.102
AND THE REST WELL,
IT'S IN STORAGE.

16:13.233 --> 16:14.756
YOU KNOW, EVERYTHING
ABOUT THIS,

16:14.886 --> 16:16.932
IT JUST, I DON'T
KNOW, IT FEELS RIGHT.

16:18.629 --> 16:20.675
DO YOU BELIEVE
IN KISMET, MITCH?

16:20.805 --> 16:21.676
YOU KNOW, I DO.

16:22.503 --> 16:23.765
AND I DO BELIEVE
THAT IT WAS FATE

16:23.895 --> 16:25.071
THAT YOU SAVED
MY LIFE TODAY.

16:25.723 --> 16:26.942
IT'S KIND OF LIKE WELL,

16:27.073 --> 16:30.424
WE, WELL, WE ALL,
WE BELONG TOGETHER.

16:30.554 --> 16:32.339
GOD, IT'S JUST SO EXCITING.

16:32.469 --> 16:33.601
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

16:33.731 --> 16:34.602
BYE!

16:38.258 --> 16:39.085
-MOM!

16:43.524 --> 16:44.612
-APRIL: MANNY!
WHAT YOU GOT?

16:45.178 --> 16:46.527
-UH, HMM.

16:47.180 --> 16:48.094
-WHAT IS THAT?

16:49.008 --> 16:49.878
-IT'S A KITE.

16:51.010 --> 16:52.098
-OH, SORRY.

16:53.186 --> 16:54.056
-WHAT IS THAT?

16:54.578 --> 16:55.927
-OH, IT'S MY BLUEPRINTS.
-OH YEAH?

16:56.058 --> 16:57.451
-LET ME SEE, HAVE A LOOK.

16:57.581 --> 16:59.279
-OH, YOU CAN'T
SEE 'EM, NO NO!
[LAUGHING]

16:59.409 --> 17:00.671
-BLUEPRINTS. FOR WHAT?

17:01.281 --> 17:02.934
-FOR MY KITE, OBVIOUSLY.

17:03.065 --> 17:04.980
I AM STUDYING
DESIGN, YOU KNOW.

17:05.111 --> 17:06.851
I'M GONNA PRACTICE BEFORE
THE ACTUAL CONTEST.

17:06.982 --> 17:08.723
-WELL, I DON'T
NEED BLUEPRINTS.

17:08.853 --> 17:11.464
-OH, YOU'RE GONNA RELY
ON ARTISTIC VISION, RIGHT?

17:11.595 --> 17:12.640
-YEAH!

17:14.032 --> 17:15.208
-WELL, IT'S VERY...

17:16.252 --> 17:17.513
WORDS FAIL ME.

17:19.167 --> 17:20.604
-WHAT DO YOU GOT?
LET ME SEE.

17:20.734 --> 17:23.041
-NO NO NO, THIS IS
